Again.

97
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:31,103
Not here.

98
00:06:33,143 --> 00:06:34,395
Not now.

99
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,027
When?

100
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:55,840
Thank you.

101
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:57,585
Give us one more smile, love.

102
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:01,463
You are yourself again.

103
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:05,804
Are you tired?

104
00:07:05,884 --> 00:07:07,682
It has been an eventful morning.

105
00:07:08,303 --> 00:07:11,432
Perhaps I should lay down,
gather my strength.

106
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:13,107
I can help Dorothy make lunch later.

107
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:14,526
DOROTHY: Of course.

108
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:46,884
She does seem better, doesn't she?

109
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:49,059
I'm praying for her.

110
00:07:50,387 --> 00:07:54,437
Our family certainly doesn't want
to have to have her locked away for good.

111
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,989
But what she is now is not acceptable.

112
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:04,283
To whom?

113
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:06,778
To us.

114
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:08,204
To anyone.

115
00:08:09,948 --> 00:08:13,998
Everett, she's a baby killer and a madwoman.

116
00:08:14,077 --> 00:08:16,921
Facts known notjust in New York anymore.

117
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:18,915
(CLEARS THROAT)

118
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,343
They're talking in Philadelphia?

119
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:26,093
Ethel's fiancé broke off their engagement.

120
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:30,807
And I'm living in hope
like some pathetic spinster.

121
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,478
GALLINGERI She will get better.

122
00:08:32,554 --> 00:08:33,897
We're all hoping.

123
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:37,521
But I know Eleanor
wouldn't want her collapse

124
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,853
to affect Ethel and me the way it has.

125
00:08:51,448 --> 00:08:52,700
We meet again.

126
00:08:53,825 --> 00:08:55,077
LUCY: Mr. Robertson.

127
00:08:57,454 --> 00:09:00,674
I saw you in here with these sick men.

128
00:09:00,749 --> 00:09:03,878
You're very good. You brighten their day.

129
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,633
Well, how could you not?

130
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:10,717
Were you referring to the comatose patient?

131
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:14,304
The men who were delirious on morphine?

132
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:16,978
Or the ones who were asleep?

133
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,234
Then you brighten mine.

134
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,484
Don't you believe me?

135
00:09:24,564 --> 00:09:26,066
I'm holding a full bedpan,

136
00:09:26,149 --> 00:09:28,527
so it's harder to believe than you realize.

137
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:32,911
Look, you're a quick
and clever girl and I like that,

138
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:36,414
but when will you stop being clever
and give me a chance?

139
00:09:36,493 --> 00:09:39,167
LUCY: There's no shortage
of not so clever nurses around here,

140
00:09:39,245 --> 00:09:40,588
all hired by you,

141
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,921
who've already given you a chance

142
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,252
and then some.

143
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:48,047
HENRY: But you're the one
that has me intrigued.

144
00:09:49,172 --> 00:09:51,095
Do you already have men courting you?

145
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:55,178
You hesitated. I'm gonna take that as a no,

146
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,514
which tells me I shouldn't give up the chase.

147
00:09:58,932 --> 00:10:01,401
Then tell me, Mr. Robertson,

148
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:05,438
do you believe in God?

149
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:09,030
Do you read the Bible,

150
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:10,827
go to church

151
00:10:10,902 --> 00:10:12,620
and lead a Christian life?

152
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,913
You're hesitating.

153
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:20,044
So, I'm gonna take that as a no.

154
00:10:20,995 --> 00:10:24,374
Which tells me you should
most definitely give up the chase.

155
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:35,678
Clara! Clara!

156
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,932
<i>THACKERY</i> ON <i>PHONE: <i>
What happened to her?</i>

157
00:10:37,011 --> 00:10:39,810
She broke into Hackett's offlce
and gave herself a heroin injection

158
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,641
big enough to kill an elephant.

159
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,601
Fucking putrid scene.

160
00:10:43,685 --> 00:10:44,982
<i>THACKERY: Where's the body now?</i>

161
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:47,109
Family is sending someone
up from the city to collect it.

162
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,482
<i>Turns out, her real name is Marianne Horner.</i>

163
00:10:49,566 --> 00:10:51,739
<i>Family's got some
big copper mining company.</i>

164
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:52,819
Absolutely not.

165
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:55,496
THACKERY: I can understand
your trepidation.

166
00:10:55,572 --> 00:10:56,698
Trepidation?

167
00:10:57,282 --> 00:10:59,376
You want to cut our dead daughter open

168
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:02,249
and root around inside her
like some jewelry box.

169
00:11:03,913 --> 00:11:07,133
It's enough that we've had to live
with her cocaine addiction.

170
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:11,680
She allowed men into her mouth
in exchange for the drug.

171
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:17,310
Our friends believe that she's
been away in Virginia at college

172
00:11:17,385 --> 00:11:19,513
and came down with the flu.

173
00:11:19,596 --> 00:11:22,190
How do you suggest we explain
that there will be no funeral

174
00:11:22,265 --> 00:11:25,610
because a doctor wants to
open her up and study her insides?

175
00:11:28,271 --> 00:11:29,488
Mrs. Horner, you feel the same?

176
00:11:30,732 --> 00:11:33,030
My wife is not in a place to think rationally.

177
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:34,861
Can't you see that?

178
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:38,956
Look, you have my heartfelt sympathies,

179
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:44,209
but you must understand that I'm trying
to save girls like your daughter with my work.

180
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:49,171
But let's be frank here,

181
00:11:49,250 --> 00:11:51,924
your daughter isn't the only person
in the family who has a problem.

182
00:11:53,588 --> 00:11:56,933
You have as much interest
in finding a cure as I do.

183
00:11:57,008 --> 00:12:00,262
You help me, and perhaps
with what I learn, I can help you.

184
00:12:03,473 --> 00:12:06,477
I'll work as fast as I can
and you can bury her in a few days.

185
00:12:07,352 --> 00:12:08,979
You won't cut her face?

186
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:13,692
I'll protect it with my life.

187
00:12:13,775 --> 00:12:15,573
You promised I'd have my fee, Mr. Cleary.

188
00:12:15,652 --> 00:12:18,997
And you'll have it. Mrs. Showalter here
is gonna cover all your costs.

189
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:22,076
You've heard of the Showalters, yeah?
Probably own this building.

190
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:25,788
Be that as it may, if I don't have the
amount at my office by tomorrow,

191
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,043
your nun will need to find another lawyer.

192
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:40,309
You didn't have to come.

193
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:42,012
I should have come sooner.

194
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:43,438
You're here now.

195
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:04,876
All rise.

196
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:09,043
The Honorable Parkinson Bothamly presiding.

197
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:12,921
Be seated.

198
00:13:15,003 --> 00:13:17,802
Mr. Whitting, you asked
for this pre-trial hearing, correct?

199
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,302
I did, Your Honor.

200
00:13:19,382 --> 00:13:24,684
In front of me are 16 past cases thrown out

201
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,981
due to proven entrapment by
the New York Vice Department.

202
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:29,400
All of which have no relevance here.

203
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:31,477
Each case on its own merits, Counselor.

204
00:13:31,561 --> 00:13:35,361
But an examination of the files
will clearly show uncommon similarities

205
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:39,741
between those wrongly accused citizens
and my client, Sister Harriet.

206
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,617
I think it only fair...

207
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:44,916
Do not tell me what is fair
in my courtroom, Mr. Whitting.

208
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:53,209
"Lo, children are a heritage from the Lord
and the fruit of the womb is His reward."

209
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,130
WHITTING: Excuse me?

210
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,927
Psalm 127.

211
00:13:57,003 --> 00:14:00,303
I'm surprised the devil allows you
to remember any verse, Miss Dolan.

212
00:14:00,882 --> 00:14:02,259
But hear me,

213
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:05,686
the devil will not influence rne
in my decisions.

214
00:14:05,762 --> 00:14:08,857
He is no more a power over me
than your pretender in Rome.

215
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:10,148
Your Honor...

216
00:14:10,224 --> 00:14:13,273
JUDGE: You have shown the true
murderous nature of your people.

217
00:14:14,645 --> 00:14:18,115
I will use this courtroom
and the strength of my God

218
00:14:18,983 --> 00:14:22,362
to sound a warning against the people
now flooding our shores

219
00:14:22,445 --> 00:14:26,040
and let real Americans
know exactly what you are.

220
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:33,005
The trial will formally commence
on the 15th.

221
00:14:34,624 --> 00:14:36,467
- Next case.
-(GAVEL BANGS)

222
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:46,810
What the fuck just happened?

223
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:54,943
<i>GALLINGER: You haven't seen
the new club yet.</i>

224
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:56,737
Yale built theirs down the street.

225
00:14:56,813 --> 00:14:58,565
It's almost 12 stories.

226
00:14:58,648 --> 00:15:01,322
But you'll see ours is far more tasteful.

227
00:15:04,153 --> 00:15:06,406
Is this how I used to do it?

228
00:15:06,489 --> 00:15:07,832
Of course.

229
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:11,620
It looks wrong to me.

230
00:15:11,702 --> 00:15:13,420
It looks lovely.

231
00:15:13,496 --> 00:15:15,169
I can start again.

232
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,419
Are you all right, Ellie?

233
00:15:20,837 --> 00:15:24,137
I just want everything
to be right for you, Everett.

234
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:27,685
You always used to love to show me off
to your classmates.

235
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:31,310
Now I'm afraid there's not much left
to brag about.

236
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:32,686
Nonsense.

237
00:15:35,143 --> 00:15:36,520
You will always be

238
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:40,026
the most beautiful girl in the world to me.

239
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:43,447
ELEANOR: But I've lost so much weight.

240
00:15:43,526 --> 00:15:46,700
My dress will be hanging off of me.

241
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,873
And my color...

242
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,746
GALLINGER: lt'sjust a...

243
00:15:50,825 --> 00:15:54,580
A class reunion with a bunch
of boring Penn Medical men

244
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:56,005
and their wives.

245
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,630
Far too many of whom
also happen to be their cousin.

246
00:15:59,709 --> 00:16:01,962
ELEANOR: What would I even say to them?

247
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:05,431
That I've recently been locked away?

248
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,133
And the dinner...

249
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:10,553
What if one of my teeth comes loose?

250
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:16,100
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

251
00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:28,363
Gallinger.

252
