00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:49,518
Don't you be sorry.

774
00:48:51,595 --> 00:48:54,474
It is not your fault you ended up here.

775
00:48:58,436 --> 00:49:00,985
Is that really what you want?

776
00:49:02,648 --> 00:49:04,241
You want to be with me?

777
00:49:06,444 --> 00:49:08,788
More than anything in the world.

778
00:49:12,366 --> 00:49:13,583
Then you will be.

779
00:49:13,868 --> 00:49:15,711
(CROWD CHEERING)

780
00:49:33,053 --> 00:49:34,475
There we go.

781
00:49:35,347 --> 00:49:37,349
That should guarantee it.

782
00:49:41,312 --> 00:49:42,905
All right, OttO.

783
00:49:43,898 --> 00:49:46,242
Let's get you delira and excira.

784
00:49:46,317 --> 00:49:47,409
Arm.

785
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:51,822
(INDISTINCT)

786
00:49:52,573 --> 00:49:55,122
You ready? Ready?
Come on! Come on! Come on!

787
00:49:55,201 --> 00:49:56,828
(CHEERING)

788
00:49:56,911 --> 00:49:58,709
No cheap shots. Shake hands.

789
00:49:58,787 --> 00:50:00,380
- CLEARY: Come on, boyo!
- Wrestle!

790
00:50:00,456 --> 00:50:03,050
CLEARY: Come on! Rip his fucking arm off!

791
00:50:04,668 --> 00:50:06,090
Yeah!

792
00:50:06,170 --> 00:50:07,763
(LAUGHING)

793
00:50:08,214 --> 00:50:11,218
Come on!

794
00:50:15,763 --> 00:50:18,141
Otto.

795
00:50:18,933 --> 00:50:20,185
Otto!

796
00:50:20,267 --> 00:50:23,441
MAN 1: Otto!
MAN 2: Come on, get up!

797
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:27,449
Shit.

798
00:50:30,528 --> 00:50:32,622
(PIG GRUNTING)

799
00:50:51,298 --> 00:50:53,972
(PIG SQUEALING)

800
00:51:00,975 --> 00:51:02,101
Here.

801
00:51:05,646 --> 00:51:07,819
One hundred and five.

802
00:51:07,898 --> 00:51:09,900
Our syphilitic sow

803
00:51:09,984 --> 00:51:12,908
is now three degrees above normal.

804
00:51:14,697 --> 00:51:17,917
We have no idea if quinine
will even cure malaria in a pig.

805
00:51:17,992 --> 00:51:19,835
Well, in five more degrees,

806
00:51:19,910 --> 00:51:22,083
we'll load her up with it and find out.

807
00:51:22,204 --> 00:51:25,003
In the meantime, we let the fever rage.

808
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:27,759
You've got a visitor.

809
00:51:27,835 --> 00:51:29,337
THACKERY: Excellent.

810
00:51:29,420 --> 00:51:30,842
Thank you, gentlemen.

811
00:51:30,921 --> 00:51:33,470
I need to begin a full dissection

812
00:51:33,549 --> 00:51:35,677
of this girl's body.

813
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:40,014
And I'll return in an hour
and take the pig's temperature.

814
00:51:40,931 --> 00:51:43,810
You know, if people actually knew
what you did in here,

815
00:51:43,892 --> 00:51:46,566
they wouldn't trust you
to give them a fucking aspirin.

816
00:51:46,645 --> 00:51:47,646
(LAUGHING)

817
00:51:58,699 --> 00:51:59,871
(PHONE RINGS)

818
00:52:03,370 --> 00:52:04,713
(PHONE RINGS)

819
00:52:10,294 --> 00:52:11,386
Yes?

820
00:52:13,088 --> 00:52:14,635
Put it through.

821
00:52:20,804 --> 00:52:22,477
(PHONE RINGS)

822
00:52:23,349 --> 00:52:24,350
(CLEARS THROAT)

823
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:28,188
Dr. Edwards speaking.

824
00:52:30,773 --> 00:52:31,899
What?

825
00:52:34,943 --> 00:52:36,286
Right now?

826
00:52:44,203 --> 00:52:46,331
MRS. EDWARDS: Have another piece
of cake. I made it myself.

827
00:52:46,413 --> 00:52:47,505
OPAL: I shouldn't.

828
00:52:47,581 --> 00:52:50,300
There's only so many pounds
a girl can dance away. (CHUCKLES)

829
00:52:50,376 --> 00:52:52,003
MRS. EDWARDS: You can afford it.

830
00:52:52,086 --> 00:52:55,135
Algie went on and on
about how pretty you were,

831
00:52:55,214 --> 00:52:57,637
but he didn't do your silhouette justice.

832
00:53:00,761 --> 00:53:02,479
(CHUCKLING)

833
00:53:03,472 --> 00:53:06,146
Algie, look who's here.

834
00:53:11,814 --> 00:53:12,940
Opal.

835
00:53:23,242 --> 00:53:24,414
Hello, sweet.

836
00:53:25,119 --> 00:53:30,797
We finally get to meet this wife of yours
after hearing about her for all these months.

837
00:53:31,291 --> 00:53:32,668
OPAL: It's been so long.

838
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:35,633
Let me get my arms around you again.

839
00:53:36,630 --> 00:53:40,635
She sailed into Boston on the Saxonia,
day before yesterday.

840
00:53:40,718 --> 00:53:42,436
Boston?

841
00:53:42,511 --> 00:53:44,934
Where I thought you would be.

842
00:53:45,013 --> 00:53:47,232
But I learned my mistake.

843
00:53:47,307 --> 00:53:49,901
This country is so big, with so many cities.

844
00:53:49,977 --> 00:53:52,150
I came here straightaway.

845
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:53,947
To my parents?

846
00:53:54,022 --> 00:53:55,615
Who greeted me like family.

847
00:53:55,691 --> 00:53:57,489
MRS. EDWARDS:
Because that's what you are.

848
00:53:58,694 --> 00:54:00,321
That's what I am.

849
00:54:02,364 --> 00:54:05,459
Also a mess after all this traveling.

850
00:54:05,534 --> 00:54:07,286
I need to freshen up a bit.

851
00:54:07,369 --> 00:54:08,916
Absence may make the heart grow fonder,

852
00:54:08,996 --> 00:54:12,216
but a little bit of lip rouge
will make the heart beat quicker.

853
00:54:13,333 --> 00:54:15,427
Down the hall, just to the right.

854
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:17,880
Won't be a moment.

855
00:54:27,890 --> 00:54:30,188
Who on earth is that woman?

856
00:54:31,810 --> 00:54:34,609
She is my wife, just as she said she is.

857
00:54:34,688 --> 00:54:38,192
You think that's something you
might want to tell us, that you got married?

858
00:54:38,275 --> 00:54:40,994
Boy, that's not something
you just forget about.

859
00:54:41,779 --> 00:54:43,247
I guess I hoped that she would.

860
00:54:43,322 --> 00:54:46,041
You should have told us. Why'd you lie?

861
00:54:50,454 --> 00:54:52,206
It happened so fast.

862
00:54:54,374 --> 00:54:56,001
We were in Paris.

863
00:54:56,794 --> 00:54:59,547
Medicine was going well.
People were accepting me.

864
00:54:59,630 --> 00:55:03,055
We met and lwas happy.

865
00:55:06,053 --> 00:55:07,646
- But then...
-"But then."

866
00:55:07,721 --> 00:55:10,144
There is always a "but then" with you.

867
00:55:10,224 --> 00:55:11,817
You run hot and then you run cold.

868
00:55:11,892 --> 00:55:13,894
And then you run and run.

869
00:55:13,977 --> 00:55:17,151
How in the world did you think
this wouldn't catch up with you?

870
00:55:17,231 --> 00:55:18,483
I don't even know what she wants.

871
00:55:18,565 --> 00:55:20,442
I know exactly what she wants.

872
00:55:20,526 --> 00:55:22,494
That girl is determined.

873
00:55:25,948 --> 00:55:27,575
What did I miss?

874
00:55:32,079 --> 00:55:33,581
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

